entries.meaning: (rare or dialectal) One's age, age in years, period of life.
(archaic or poetic) Old age, senility; an old person.
examples: Synonyms: elderliness; see also Thesaurus:old age, Thesaurus:old person

entries.meaning: (archaic or poetic) Time; an age, an indefinitely long period of time.
(archaic or poetic) Former ages, antiquity, olden times.
examples: Synonyms: days of yore; see also Thesaurus:the past

verbs.description: eld (third-person singular simple present elds, present participle elding, simple past and past participle elded)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, archaic, poetic or dialectal) To age, become or grow old.
(intransitive, archaic or poetic) To delay; linger.
(transitive, archaic or poetic) To make old, age.
